      • setPersistentData

        public void setPersistentData(java.lang.String key,
                              java.lang.Object persistentData)
        This method is usable by subclasses to store any type of serializable data. This intention is to provide a mechanism for publisher RTs to be able to persist data between runs. Normally this method would at least be called in the terminate method, but may also be called regularly for failover purposes.
